      <!-- Numerology Basics -->
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="basics">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h3>What is numerology?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Numerology is the study of numbers and their energetic influence on human life. It is based on the belief that numbers carry specific vibrations that can reveal information about a person's character, purpose, motivations, and path in life. Numerology can be used to gain insights into various aspects of life including relationships, career, and personal growth.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="basics">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h3>What is the history of numerology?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Numerology has ancient roots that can be traced back to several civilizations including Babylonia, ancient Egypt, ancient China, and ancient India. The modern system of Western numerology is often credited to Pythagoras, the Greek mathematician and philosopher who lived in the 6th century BCE. In India, numerology has been practiced for thousands of years as part of Vedic mathematics and astrology.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="basics">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h3>Is numerology a science or a spiritual practice?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Numerology is considered a metaphysical science or spiritual practice rather than a conventional science. While it uses mathematical calculations, it is based on the mystical and symbolic properties of numbers rather than empirical scientific methods. Many people find value in numerology as a tool for self-discovery and personal growth.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="basics">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h3>How does numerology relate to Indian culture and traditions?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>In Indian culture, numerology (known as "Ank Shastra" in Hindi) has been practiced for thousands of years and is closely tied to Vedic astrology (Jyotish). It is often used in naming ceremonies, determining auspicious dates for important events, and understanding one's destiny. Many Indian families consult numerologists for naming their children, businesses, and even for selecting house numbers that will bring positive energy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="basics">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h3>What are the core numbers in numerology?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>The core numbers in numerology include: Life Path Number (derived from birth date), Destiny/Expression Number (derived from full birth name), Soul Urge/Heart's Desire Number (derived from vowels in name), Personality Number (derived from consonants in name), and Birth Day Number (the day of the month you were born). Each of these numbers reveals different aspects of your character and life journey.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Calculations -->
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="calculations">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h3>How is the Life Path Number calculated?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>The Life Path Number is calculated by reducing your full birth date to a single digit (or master number). For example, if you were born on September 15, 1985, you would calculate: 9 (month) + 1+5 (day) + 1+9+8+5 (year) = 38. Then reduce: 3+8 = 11. Since 11 is a master number, you can keep it as 11, or further reduce: 1+1 = 2. Your Life Path Number would be 11/2.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="calculations">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h3>How is the Destiny/Expression Number calculated?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>The Destiny Number is calculated by assigning numerical values to each letter in your full birth name and then reducing the sum to a single digit (or master number). In the Pythagorean system: A=1, B=2, C=3, D=4, E=5, F=6, G=7, H=8, I=9, J=1, K=2, and so on. Add all the numbers together and reduce to a single digit or master number.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="calculations">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h3>What are master numbers in numerology?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>Master numbers in numerology are 11, 22, and 33. These numbers are not reduced to a single digit because they are considered to have special significance and power. They represent a higher spiritual plane and indicate potential for spiritual growth and achievement. People with master numbers in their core numerology chart often face greater challenges but also have greater potential for achievement.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="calculations">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h3>Should I use my current name or birth name for calculations?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>For most numerology calculations, your birth name (the name given to you at birth) is used to calculate your Destiny/Expression Number, Soul Urge Number, and Personality Number as these relate to your inherent qualities and life purpose. However, if you've legally changed your name and use it consistently, this new name can also be analyzed to understand how it might be influencing your current life path and experiences.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item" data-category="calculations">
        <div class="faq-question">
          <h3>How do I calculate my Personal Year Number?</h3>
          <span class="faq-toggle"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer">
          <p>To calculate your Personal Year Number, add the month and day of your birth to the current year. For example, if you were born on May 15 and the current year is 2025, you would calculate: 5 (May) + 1+5 (day) + 2+0+2+5 (year) = 20. Then reduce: 2+0 = 2. Your Personal Year Number for 2025 would be 2, indicating a year focused on relationships, patience, and cooperation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
